# Invoice Application — Playwright Test Automation

## Application
App URL: https://apps.powerapps.com/play/e/5ae6e1b2-1834-e538-87c8-7bea27dfc2db/a/f6aa60b5-4c74-48f6-87af-9623b4417105?tenantId=18323149-cc4d-4bff-809d-3eda6caec73a
The app is a Power Apps Canvas Application.
It renders ENTIRELY inside: iframe[name="fullscreen-app-host"]
Every locator MUST go through this frame locator first.
NEVER write locators directly on the page object for Canvas app elements.

## Authentication
Auth is handled via storageState: auth.json in playwright.config.ts.
Tests never need a login step — the saved session handles it automatically.
NEVER add login code to any test file.
auth.json must NEVER be committed to git — it is already in .gitignore.

## Dataverse Backend
Dataverse URL: https://dev-itt-apps.crm8.dynamics.com
Invoice table EntitySetName: dia_invoicedetailses
Invoice status field: dia_status (plain text, NOT a choice column)
Status values: Draft, Submitted, Reviewed, Approved, Flagged,
  Cancelled, Sent, Fail-Creation, Fail-Update, Fail-Flag, Fail-Approval, Fail-Review
Failed on Dashboard = Fail-Creation OR Fail-Update OR Fail-Flag OR Fail-Approval OR Fail-Review
Billing cycle: 6th of current month to 5th of NEXT month (not calendar month)
Date field for filtering: dia_invoicedate
Tenant ID: 18323149-cc4d-4bff-809d-3eda6caec73a

## Token Capture Pattern
Dataverse uses a Bearer token intercepted from Canvas app network traffic.
Pattern: page.on("request") listening for crm8.dynamics.com with Authorization: Bearer header.
Always use type Request from @playwright/test for the callback parameter.
Token capture happens in test.beforeAll so it runs once for the whole describe block.

## Coding Rules — Always Follow These
1. Import: import { test, expect, request, type Page, type FrameLocator, type Request } from "@playwright/test"
2. Always use page.frameLocator('iframe[name="fullscreen-app-host"]') before any Canvas element locator
3. NEVER hardcode count values — use regex patterns like /\d+\s*Drafts/
4. NEVER use waitForTimeout except inside getDashboardTaskCount helper
5. Use getByRole and getByText — NEVER use auto-generated CSS IDs or appmagic IDs
6. Use expect.soft for all UI structure visibility assertions
7. Use hard expect for interaction and navigation assertions
8. getByLabel does NOT work in Canvas apps — use getByPlaceholder or getByText
9. Canvas toggles are custom controls — click the label text to toggle them
10. Canvas rich text areas are contenteditable — use .fill() then toHaveValue()
11. Delete buttons in Canvas are image icons — use getByRole('img') not getByRole('button')

## Project Structure
tests/dashboard.spec.ts — Dashboard UI and Dataverse validation — 13 tests all passing
tests/create-invoice-adhoc.spec.ts — Create Invoice adhoc flow — UI interaction tests
tests/smoke.spec.ts — Basic app load and login session verification
tests/seed.spec.ts — Template file used by AI — do not edit manually
specs/ — Test plan markdown files written during planning
playwright.config.ts — headless false, storageState auth.json, chromium only, retries 1

## Working Helper Functions in This Project
openDashboard(page) — navigates to app URL, waits for Dashboard text, returns appFrame
openCreateInvoice(page) — navigates to app URL, clicks Create Invoice, returns appFrame
getBillingCycleDates() — returns start and end ISO date strings for current billing cycle
getDataverseCount(token, filterExpression) — calls Dataverse API with filter, returns count
getDashboardTaskCount(page, appFrame, labelPattern) — waits for Invoice Tasks section, reads count
getLineItemCount(appFrame) — counts line item rows on Create Invoice form using Find items text